{"id":4633,"global_id":"www.unitingnc.org?id=4633","global_id_lineage":["www.unitingnc.org?id=4633"],"author":"25","status":"publish","date":"2019-01-14 13:31:14","date_utc":"2019-01-14 18:31:14","modified":"2019-01-14 13:31:14","modified_utc":"2019-01-14 18:31:14","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/stand-with-us\/january-27-understanding-the-plight-of-migrants-charlotte\/","rest_url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-json\/tribe\/events\/v1\/events\/4633","title":"January 27: Understanding the Plight of Migrants (Charlotte)","description":"<p>Migrants are in need of support in Charlotte.<\/p>\n<p>Come find out more about the plight of migrants coming into the U.S. and get plugged into how you can help right here at home.<\/p>\n<p>Join us as we discuss the migrants\u2019 situation at the border; the relief work being done at the Charlotte Greyhound bus station; and what happens at the end of the migrant families\u2019 journey. Meet other community members who have been active at the Greyhound station and find out how you can get involved.<\/p>\n<p>Please bring your choice of the following to the event (we are using every opportunity to collect for the migrants):<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Hats, gloves, socks, coats<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Toothbrushes, toothpaste, dental floss<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Deodorant (men&#8217;s and women&#8217;s)<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Lip balm such as Chapstick<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Coloring books with little packs of crayons for kids<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Little fun toys to keep kids occupied during the long bus ride<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Little packages of Kleenex<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Bottled water<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Adult and children\u2019s cold medicines<\/p>\n<p>\u25cf Snacks &#8211; non-perishable food that&#8217;s easy to travel with. Example: animal crackers, trail mix, Cliff bars, Cheezits<\/p>","excerpt":"<a href=\"\" class=\"more-link\" title=\"Read More\">Read More<\/a>","slug":"january-27-understanding-the-plight-of-migrants-charlotte","image":{"url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/w